begin_memory_text: At the beginning of our conversation, my conversation partner and I talked about our days and introduced ourselves to each other. I spoke about school and my conversation partner spoke about working from home.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, my conversation partner and I talked about part-time jobs. I spoke about working at the grocery store as a college student and my conversation partner talked about the part-time job held at a hardware store during their time in college.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation, my conversation partner and I spoke about our experiences working in retail, our opinions on name-brand items versus their generic counterparts, and what our home towns are like.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going fairly well. I expect it to be pretty average in comparison to my other weeks. It might be more relaxed and enjoyable than the previous week because I have less school work to do this week and our midterm exams are over.
critical_positive: things that worked well about the conversation included our age range, interests, experiences, and how familiar we each were with using video conference software to have a conversation. My conversation partner and I seemed within 5-7 years of age to each other, which made me feel comfortable when speaking to them. We have both worked in retail and likely have similar political opinions which helped the conversation.
critical_negative: something that did not work as well in the conversation I just had was the difference between where we each are within our lives. my conversation partner had recently gotten married and is working full time living with their spouse. on the other hand, I am still in college as a full-time student and I live with roommates. the difference between where we're each at in our lives was interesting

begin_memory_text: We talked about school and our jobs and just got to know each other - they were a public health major so we talked about their lives with COVID-19.
middle_memory_text: At this point in the conversation we were mostly discussing COVID-19 and how it affected both of us, since we're several years apart in age.
end_memory_text: We talked more about COVID and the stupid people that live around us, and how they're handling things. We also talked about my wedding since I got married right before the pandemic hit.
rest_of_day_open: Since it's Monday, there's a lot of ways this week can go. But I've also managed to complete a big project for work today and I have a potential interview tomorrow, so I'm excited to see what the next few days bring. I'm hoping that this week will give me a chance to relax and reconnect with my husband as well.
critical_positive: My conversation partner and I had a lot to talk about, despite knowing hardly anything about one another. We were able to find topics to discuss without having too much downtime or feeling like the conversation was forced. It was fun to get to 'meet' someone I didn't know since I don't get to do that often with COVID going on.
critical_negative: It's sometimes hard to come up with conversation with someone you don't know well. It can also be difficult to talk to a stranger online because you're not sure how much information you want to reveal about yourself, so that limits your options as well. I also am always afraid the person is serially annoyed with me.
